<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881024-0047 </DOCNO><HL> Justice O'Connor Has Breast Cancer Surgery </HL><SO> </SO><G> SUP </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Supreme Court Justice Sandra O'Connor underwent surgery for breast cancer, but said in a statement released at the court that the &quot;prognosis is for total recovery.&quot;    Her statement didn't include any details as to the severity of the cancer or the extent of the surgery, but she did say it was &quot;in a very early form and stage.&quot; The surgery was performed Friday afternoon at Georgetown University Hospital.    The statement said Justice O'Connor doesn't expect to miss any oral arguments. The court is in the middle of a two-week recess, and is due to resume hearing arguments next Monday.    Justice O'Connor, appointed by President Reagan in 1981, is 58 years old and is the first woman to serve on the high court. </TEXT></DOC>